From a5e4e2254116a46227b0ff3d114128d5d05370ab Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 13 Jun 2026 21:35:18 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: add missing usd_to_toman_rate to Settings; refactor
 cache policy

The composition root read settings.usd_to_toman_rate, but the field was
never added to Settings, so the app crashed at startup with a raw
AttributeError (caught by mypy and a live run). Add the field, parse and
validate USD_TO_TOMAN_RATE from the environment with a clearly-approximate
fallback (ADR-005 / TD-04).

Also:
- extract the duplicated TTL freshness check from both services into a
  shared services/cache_policy.is_fresh helper
- add tests/test_config.py covering Settings.from_env defaults, overrides,
  validation, and directory creation (the gap that let this bug ship)
- sync .env.example with documented variables; drop the unused API_ENV
- remove a stray code fence in the logger docstring
- fix import ordering in test_services.py (ruff)

https://claude.ai/code/session_01VqntLpuy6RCbwfPZeMi68S
